<article>
    <h1>In&#xAD;vest&#xAD;ing in the fu&#xAD;ture</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201212/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-12"><time>2020-12-12</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG STORY</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Sin­ga­pore is pump­ing $25 bil­lion into sci­ence and tech­nol­ogy re­search over the next five years. Sha­bana Begum and Ch­eryl Tan look at where the money is go­ing, and how re­search into four key ar­eas can help the coun­try tackle the chal­lenges of the fu­ture.</p>
    <p>Man­u­fac­tur­ing, trade and con­nec­tiv­ity</p>
    <p>• With the world con­nected in ways it has never been be­fore, Sin­ga­pore is look­ing to en­hance its man­u­fac­tur­ing sec­tor, and also strengthen its links with the rest of the world.</p>
    <p>• This in­cludes boost­ing ca­pa­bil­i­ties in avi­a­tion, sea trans­port, lo­gis­tics and whole­sale trade.</p>
    <p>• For in­stance, Sin­ga­pore wants to en­hance the ca­pa­bil­i­ties of the avi­a­tion and mar­itime sec­tors through ad­vanced air traf­fic man­age­ment and au­to­ma­tion of air­port and sea port op­er­a­tions.</p>
    <p>Ex­am­ple: Air Traf­fic Man­age­ment Re­search In­sti­tute at Nanyang Tech­no­log­i­cal Univer­sity</p>
    <p>• Re­searchers are look­ing to lever­age ar­ti­fi­cial in­tel­li­gence to en­hance air traf­fic con­trollers’ sit­u­a­tional aware­ness and im­prove de­ci­sion-mak­ing, us­ing in­sights and pre­dic­tions gleaned from data.</p>
    <p>• For in­stance, to im­prove air­port op­er­a­tions, an air­port sur­face move­ment sim­u­la­tor can pre­dict how long it takes for a plane to move on the ground be­fore take-off and af­ter land­ing.</p>
    <p>• The in­sti­tute will also ex­plore un­manned traf­fic man­age­ment so­lu­tions as more drones and pi­lot­less aerial ve­hi­cles may be part of the airspace in the fu­ture.</p>

